==Awards and nominations==

===AMP Award===
The Australian Music Prize (AMP) is presented annually from 2005 and is sponsored by the Phonographic Performance Company of Australia (PPCA).
|-
| 2007 || &quot;Somewhere, Anywhere&quot; – New Buffalo || Australian Music Prize || 
| 2010 || &quot;Heart That&#x27;s Pounding&quot; – Sally Seltmann || Australian Music Prize || 
===APRA Awards===
The APRA Awards are presented annually from 1982 by the Australasian Performing Right Association (APRA), &quot;honouring composers and songwriters&quot;.
|-
| 2001 || Sally Russell || Professional Development Awards – Pop/Dance Music || 
| rowspan=&quot;2&quot;| 2008 || Sally Seltmann || Breakthrough Songwriter of the Year || 
| &quot;1234&quot; – Feist (Sally Seltmann, Leslie Feist) || Song of the Year || 
===ARIA Awards===

The ARIA Music Awards are presented annually from 1987 by the Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA).
|-
| 2007 || &quot;Somewhere, Anywhere&quot; – New Buffalo || Best Adult Contemporary Album || 
| 2019
| &quot;Wild Seeds&quot; (as part of Seeker Lover Keeper)
| Best Adult Contemporary Album
|-
| 2020
| &quot;The Letdown (Music from Seasons 1+2)&quot; 
| Best Original Soundtrack, Cast or Show Album


